    {
        "url": "/quotes/henry_giroux_694481",
        "quote": "As the humanities and liberal arts are downsized, privatized, and commodified, higher education finds itself caught in the paradox of claiming to invest in the future of young people while offering them few intellectual, civic, and moral supports.",
